refentry.refsect1:
&ref.title.note;
A level can be specified, which controls at what logging level the message is filtered at.
The task can also echo to a file, in which case the option to append rather than overwrite the file is available, and the level option is ignored

&ref.title.attributes;


  Attributes for EchoTask

  &taskAttributes.table.titlesLine.all;



    msg

    String

    The string that is to be send to the
    output.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;




    message

    String

    Alias for msg.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.yes;




    file

    String

    The file to write the message to.

    &attributes.defaultValue.NA;

    &attributes.required.no;




    append

    Boolean

    Append to an existing file?

    false

    &attributes.required.no;




    level

    String

    Control the level at which this message is
    reported. One of error, warning,
    info, verbose, debug.

    info

    &attributes.required.no;
